$ sudo apt update

$ sudo apt install qemu-kvm libvirt-daemon-system libvirt-clients bridge-utils

$ sudo adduser ‘username’ libvirt // Type your user name in the place of username

$ sudo adduser ‘[username]’ kvm // Here also write your username

$ sudo systemctl status libvirtd

Press Q
if virtualization is not active use following command
$sudo systemctl enable --now libvirtd

$sudo apt install virt-manager

$ sudo virt-manager
Done follow the next steps
